pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces several enhancements and refactors across the codebase, focusing on privacy/structured data, improved consent banner accessibility and progressive enhancement, custom scrollbar utilities, and the addition of a new projects showcase section. The changes improve semantic data, user experience, accessibility, and code maintainability.

**Privacy & Structured Data Improvements**
* Added `assets/privacy-structured-data.json` and `assets/structured-data.json` to provide Schema.org structured data for privacy policy and personal profile, improving SEO and semantic clarity. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-37e95d53b9488d0fec4c0f0708bc6a206601e165059d84299714cd822a526191R1-R10) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-5137a273973618b9b8ed7bd64a3389fac73e26243808d9ddaceb56882944c182R1-R8)

**Consent Banner & Dialog Accessibility and Progressive Enhancement**
* Refactored `css/components/consent-banner.css` to use progressive enhancement for backgrounds and blur effects, improved focus styles, added keyboard accessibility, and enhanced support for reduced motion and high contrast users. Also added `.no-js` and `.js` classes for toggling settings visibility, and improved print handling. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9L51-R69) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9L134-R171) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R274-R284) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R311-R316) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9L326-R381) [[6]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R416-R427) [[7]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R477-R495) [[8]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9L476-R543) [[9]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R615-L629) [[10]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R687-R694) [[11]](diffhunk://#diff-acd05e3e38f08d9d99a9e47e1753a824658a57a56ca14ba0e3aee39fbf968ce9R710-R795)

* Added a new analytics switch control with custom styles for toggling consent, including accessibility and responsive design improvements.

**Custom Scrollbar Utilities**
* Updated `css/components/custom-scrollbar.css` to add `.hide-scrollbar` utility for element-specific scrollbar hiding, and a global opt-in class for site-wide hidden scrollbars, improving flexibility and cross-browser support. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-df94d51c46a47e3d4b7a75545ac83f1e5ec88ea5a912b6f6d5f25f9a5482b8e3R53-R72) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-df94d51c46a47e3d4b7a75545ac83f1e5ec88ea5a912b6f6d5f25f9a5482b8e3L109-R137)

**Projects Showcase Section**
* Added a new projects section to `css/components/hero.css`, including responsive grid, card styles, and focus/hover effects for improved presentation and accessibility.

**Minor Variable Addition**
* Added a serif font variable `--font-serif` in `css/base/variables.css` for improved typography options.

**Other**
* Removed the `.vscode/tasks.json` file, cleaning up unused editor configuration.

issue.title: Fix fetch() calls for virtual files in multi-file mode with context-aware path resolution

comment.body:
> @copilot In multi-file mode, using `new Audio()` and `new Image()` in the JavaScript code to load data from a panel audio or image file doesn’t seem to work. Please fix this. Here’s a simple examp...

Fixed! The issue where `new Audio()` and `new Image()` couldn't load data from virtual panel files in multi-file mode has been resolved.

**Solution implemented:**
- Added Audio constructor override to intercept `new Audio(src)` calls and check virtual file system
- Added Image constructor override to intercept `new Image()` and src property setting
- Both use the same context-aware path resolution as the existing fetch override
- Creates blob URLs for virtual files and falls back to original behavior for external files

**How it works now:**
```javascript
// These now work with virtual files in multi-file mode:
const audio = new Audio('audio/song.mp3');  // Loads from virtual file system
const img = new Image();
img.src = 'images/photo.jpg';               // Also loads from virtual files
```

The constructors seamlessly handle both virtual panel files and external URLs, enabling realistic multi-file development workflows with media assets.

pull_request.title: docs: Add external protocol validation tool documentation
pull_request.body:
## Overview

This PR adds comprehensive arc42 documentation for the external protocol validation tool decision and implementation strategy.

## Changes Made

### ADR-010: External Protocol Validation Tool
- Documents architectural decision to create sophisticated Python TCP client test tool
- Explains context: hex-based protocol validation and performance testing requirements
- Details tool characteristics: external black-box testing, statistical analysis, CI integration
- Positions tool as external validation infrastructure (not architectural component)

### Chapter 8: Testing and Validation Strategy
- Added comprehensive testing and validation strategy section
- Documents protocol format specifications: `#` + 4 hex digits + payload + `!\r\n`
- Defines test scenario categories: compliance, performance, reliability testing
- Describes statistical analysis framework and development workflow integration

### Chapter 11: Enhanced Risk Management
- **Updated R-008** (Industrial Performance Requirements): Added external validation as mitigation
- **Added R-009** (Protocol Implementation Compliance): New technical risk with systematic validation approach
- Enhanced risk mitigation plans to include external validation deployment
- Updated monitoring processes to track validation results and performance baselines

## Technical Context

The external validation tool addresses critical system validation needs:

- **Protocol Compliance**: Systematic validation of hex message format adherence
- **Performance Benchmarking**: 500kBaud throughput and <5ms latency measurement
- **Stress Testing**: System behavior under load, concurrent connections, error scenarios
- **Regression Detection**: Automated validation for continuous integration

## Implementation Scope

Tool characteristics defined in documentation:
- Python TCP client connecting to UART2ETH ports 4001-4004
- Comprehensive test scenarios: valid/invalid messages, performance stress testing
- Statistical analysis: throughput (kbytes/s), latency percentiles (min/median/max RTT)
- Integration with existing logging infrastructure via `persistent_uart_logger.sh`

## Risk Mitigation

This documentation directly addresses:
- **R-008**: Performance requirements validation through external measurement
- **R-009**: Protocol implementation compliance through systematic format testing
- Establishes foundation for comprehensive external validation capability

## Next Steps

Following TDD approach:
1. Implement Python test tool with comprehensive test scenarios
2. Integrate with CI/build validation process  
3. Establish performance baselines and regression detection

---

**Documentation Reference**: ADR-010, Chapter 8 (Testing Strategy), Chapter 11 (Risk Management)

issue.body:
redis 7.4+ introduced HFE, i. e., hash / listpack with field expiration, with type identifier 22, 23, 24, and 25 in rdb format 12.

this add basic support for rdb 12 compatible with redis 7.4+,

a) HashObjectEx type, which can be formatted as json, as well as RESP commands (obj2cmd)
b) decoding hash / listpack HFE from rdb
c) encoding HashObjectEx as rdb (hash HFE)

pull_request.title: Update deprecated google-gemini/gemini-cli-action to google-github-actions/run-gemini-cli (v2)
pull_request.body:
## Summary
- Replace deprecated `google-gemini/gemini-cli-action@main` with the official `google-github-actions/run-gemini-cli@v0`
- Update parameter names: `GEMINI_API_KEY` → `gemini_api_key`, `settings_json` → `settings`
- Fix absolute file path requirements for `write_file` operations
- Maintain all existing functionality and behavior for PR reviews

## Changes Made
- Updated action reference in `.github/workflows/gemini-pr-review.yml`
- Updated parameter names to match new action's API
- Fixed file path to use absolute paths (`/tmp/review.md`) for write operations
- Updated comment to reflect migration from deprecated action

## Test Plan
- [x] Branch created and pushed successfully  
- [x] Fixed file path issue identified in previous attempt
- [ ] PR workflow triggers and runs without errors
- [ ] Gemini PR review functionality works as expected

## Migration Details
The old `google-gemini/gemini-cli-action` has been deprecated in favor of the official Google GitHub Actions version. The new action has stricter requirements:
- Requires absolute file paths for `write_file` operations
- Uses `gemini_api_key` instead of `GEMINI_API_KEY` parameter  
- Uses `settings` instead of `settings_json` parameter

This migration ensures continued functionality and compatibility with future updates.
